   ## General Facilitator Information
  * Workshops will be 1.5 or 3 hours in length and may be repeated 1-8 times throughout the conference.
  * Workshops targeting youth and young adults are preferred, though each year a few chaperone workshops are selected.
  * Preference is given towards workshops that demonstrate a high-level of interaction and share best practices/successful approaches.
  * Preference is given towards workshops that require little to no audio/visual aids (i.e. projectors, microphones, TV/DVD Players etc.)
  * once you have completed the online application potential facilitators **must call Della (250-388-5522 ext.210) before the deadline of November 4th, 2016** to verify their application before it is considered by the youth steering committee.
  * Facilitators are informed if they were chosen to host a workshop: November 30, 2016.
  * You will also receive a confirmation email that you submitted an application. Be sure you receive that in your inbox or spam. If you did not please call Della (250-388-5522 ext.210) to confirm we received your application.
  * You will be required to fulfill a Criminal Record Check if your workshop is accepted.


